sentences: Gerald Veasley (born July 28, 1955) is an American jazz bass guitarist.
He worked with Joe Zawinul from 1988 to 1995, and began releasing his own records in 1992.
He worked with Joe Zawinul from 1988 to 1995, and began releasing his own records in 1992.
His 2008 release Your Move hit No. 12 on the U.S. Billboard Top Contemporary Jazz Albums chart.
In 2002 Veasley founded his own Bass Bootcamp in Philadelphia with Roxanne Veasley and Lee Patterson.
In 1988, Gerald joined a jazz fusion band called The Zawinul Syndicate featuring keyboardist Joe Zawinul, former member of the group Weather Report.
In June of 1999, Gerald was featured playing bass on an album with Philip Bailey called “Dreams”.
On April 1, 2008, Gerald was invited on stage as a guest with Victor Wooten, along with Anthony Wellington at The Keswick Theatre in Glenside, PA
In 2019, Veasley was invited to Ridley Park, Pennsylvania to play at Ridley High School at their yearly “Jazz Night”.

The camp lasts for 2 days and students are taught many important musical skills by the instructors such as:learning how to groove, creating bass lines, improving your ear, optimizing practice time, and playing live with a drummer.
In June of 1999, Gerald was featured playing bass on an album with Philip Bailey called “Dreams”.
In 2019, Veasley was invited to Ridley Park, Pennsylvania to play at Ridley High School at their yearly “Jazz Night”.
The night featured 3 performances done by Ridley Elementary, Middle School, and High School Jazz band with Veasley playing with each group, as well as the high school acappela group; Rhapsody.
